parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling due to Spark Plug and Ignition System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalls or dies while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Starter failure can leave the driver stranded, unable to start the engine, and may cause inconvenience and safety risks.
symptoms: clicking sound when trying to start the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
Alternator belt failure can cause the alternator to fail, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise from the engine
visible signs of belt wear or damage

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to an unexpected stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when stopping at intersections or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls when stopping at intersections or stop signs
the vehicle loses power and comes to an unexpected stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs, engine damage, or even engine failure, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the water pump makes a loud noise
the temperature gauge rises to the red zone.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front struts can cause a loss of vehicle control, reduced handling, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving
the front of the vehicle sags or leans
the vehicle has uneven tire wear
the vehicle has a rough ride
the strut mounts are broken or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle is difficult to start
the vehicle hesitates or stumbles when accelerating
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the fuel pump relay clicks repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake hoses can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a spongy brake pedal, increased stopping distances, and potentially, accidents or injuries.
symptoms: brake pedal travels further than usual
